    "created_at": "2015-07-13T12:39:26Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-13T14:44:24Z",
    "body": "AHA! - that makes sense - thanks for that!\n\nUpdated to add:\nWhilst it's possible to overwrite the active app.asar (using original-fs or a spawned command-line), it does cause the current electron instance to crash (not really surprising I guess?)\n\nI assume there's no way around that - the current design of Electron doesn't allow-it to update it's own asar files - thus it becomes reliant on an outside update mechanism.\n\nWhy does no-one consider this stuff - it's 2015, not 1980 - an framework incapable of self-update isn't really much of a framework.\n\nI raised a separate issue on what dirs/asars electron looks for - a possible solution lies in expanding that perhaps - but other solutions would be nice (as is, it's a gaping hole in what Electron does tho)\n"
  },
