    "created_at": "2015-07-15T20:05:54Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-07-15T20:05:54Z",
    "body": "Replacing the `asar` file when app is running will never be supported in Electron, it is like replacing the `.exe` or `.dll` when the program is running, which is very likely to cause troubles.\n\nOnly updating the asar file in auto updater sounds an interesting idea, but it can implemented as a node module instead of a built-in feature, and I think it can be a part of the [runtime mode](https://github.com/atom/electron/issues/673) instead of a feature of Electron, so I'm merging this to #673.\n"
  },
