    "body": "I never did get a solid working solution - working with scripts to close\nthe application, swap the file and re-run it would 'sometimes' work.\n\nWhat's really needed is a system within the executable which looks for an\n'upgrade' asar file when it runs and swaps that with the current ASAR - and\na command to restart the current executable really.\n\nAnything else will be - at best - a bodge...\n\nOn 22 January 2016 at 17:36, Tomás Correia Marques <notifications@github.com\n\n> wrote:\n> \n> @shrewdlogarithm https://github.com/shrewdlogarithm I'm also having\n> this issue, can you explain how you were able to overwrite the active\n> app.asar?\n> \n> —\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n> https://github.com/atom/electron/issues/2198#issuecomment-173987533.\n"
